 :tx/rationale "MULTI-MEMBERSHIP CONCEPT ARCHITECTURE: The DOGFOOD-4 skew reveals that flat single-assignment classification is the structural bottleneck, not flat-vs-hierarchical. Concepts are regions in embedding space with fuzzy boundaries. An observation can belong to MULTIPLE concepts simultaneously — 'ignored error returns in cascade' is simultaneously about anomalies AND dependencies AND components. The natural structure is a SIMPLICIAL COMPLEX, not a tree. Observations are vertices, concepts are simplices, edges are weighted by cosine similarity. The topology EMERGES from co-occurrence: coupled concepts share members, nested concepts have subset members, bridges span disjoint concepts. CONTEXTUAL CONTINGENCY: The concept topology depends on the PERSPECTIVE (ADR-FOUNDATION-016 observation-projection duality). Same observation, different agent → different relevant concepts. Concepts form a PRESHEAF over perspectives, not a fixed object. IMPLEMENTATION: (1) assign_to_concept returns Vec of ALL matches above threshold, not single best. (2) Write multiple :exploration/concept Refs per observation (schema already supports Many). (3) Each matched concept gets centroid updated. (4) Co-occurrence structure computed at status time (Jaccard of member sets). (5) Steering uses topological features: bridges, hubs, subset nesting. PREDICTED IMPACT: The invariants skew (25/29) would become invariants+dependencies (12 dual-members), invariants+anomalies (8 dual), invariants+components (5 dual) — revealing the STRUCTURE of the domain, not flattening it into one bucket."
